qas.question: What kingdom came to power in Assam?
What was the span of time fro the Ahom Kingdom?
What event caused the end of Ahom rule in Assam?
With what religion did the Ahom merge?
What group repeatedly tried and failed to conquer the Ahom?

context: <a0_0>Ahom Kingdom<a0_0/> (<a1_0>1228–1826<a1_0/>) was a kingdom and tribe which rose to prominence in present-day Assam early in the thirteenth century. They ruled much of Assam from the 13th century until the establishment of <a2_0>British rule<a2_0/> in 1838. The Ahoms brought with them a tribal religion and a language of their own, however they later merged with the <a3_0>Hindu<a3_0/> religion. From thirteenth till seventeenth century, repeated attempts were made by the <a4_0>Muslim rulers of Delhi<a4_0/> to invade and subdue Ahoms, however the Ahoms managed to maintain their independence and ruled themselves for nearly 600 years.
